    <div class="centerimg">
        <img src="images/gaze.jpg" alt="gaze" title="gaze" style="width:600px;height:auto;border:1mm solid rgba(190, 190, 190, .6);filter: drop-shadow(0px 0px 0px black);">
    </div>

    <div>

            <p class="par2">
            I'm a composer, clarinetist and saxophonist based in Los Angeles, CA. I recently graduated from the <a href="https://music.arts.uci.edu/icit/">Integrated Composition, Improvisation and Technology</a> PhD program at <a href="https://uci.edu/">UC Irvine</a> where I specialized in 20th- and 21st-century music notations. My dissertation "<i>Scoring the Unknown: Rethinking Fixity and Openness in Western Art Music Notation</i>" is now available via UCI's library and ProQuest (<a href="./diss.html">as well as on this site</a>).
            </p>
            <p class="par2">
            In 2018, I got my MFA in Music Performance and Literature from Mills College (<a href="https://www.oaklandca.gov/news/2022/oakland-city-council-votes-to-urge-investigation-into-mills-college-closure"><i>requiescat in pace</i></a>) where I studied composition/improvisation with Roscoe Mitchell, James Fei, Fred Frith, and Zeena Parkins. 
            </p>
            <p class="par2">
            I tend to be most interested in musical modernism, hybrid music notations, algorithmic composition, cross-modal fixed/free musics, the American jazz tradition and the music of the AACM. I'm also a passable guitarist, draughtsman and film photographer.
            </p>

        <hr>
    </div>

